cs.CV, cs.IR, cs.LG, cs.MM, cs.NE 

This paper is about unsupervised hashing for large-scale image retrieval, which involves computer vision (CV) and information retrieval (IR) techniques. Therefore, cs.CV and cs.IR are the most likely sub-categories. The paper also proposes a neural network-based model and formulates a training objective, which are related to machine learning (LG) and multimedia (MM). Additionally, the paper mentions the use of a graph-based search procedure, which is a common technique in neural networks (NE).
